<br>
Some of us can't afford or have time to play two pay-for-play games, or even 'try it and see'.  I barely have time for one character on a &quot;normal&quot; server and one on Firiona Vie!  I've no problem with DAoC...it looks like a cool game, and I'm happy that some people want to play it and EQ, or even DAoC instead, but why do people insist on spreading the joys of DAoC all over EQ message boards, and sneering at the 'idiots still taking whatever crap Verant feeds them'?<br>
<br>
I realize this thread was perhaps started for different reasons - it *does*, perhaps, give us leverage with Verant to push for a real RP server.  Jantis hit the nail on the head - they did a half-arsed job on Firiona Vie by making it &quot;RP preferred&quot; so as to A. Not piss anyone off and B. Not have to work to enforce anything.  It's so obvious they can hardly argue that they didn't do it so as to minimize their workload.<br>
<br>
That's not to say that telling them this would accomplish anything, but I still keep making my thoughts known to them.  I'm not expecting them to listen, per se, but I keep trying.<br>
<br>
Yet despite it all, I'm sticking it out.  I like EQ, generally.  I like Firiona Vie even more...hell, I've had some really fun experiences so far.  I bet I'd like DAoC just as much, if not more, but I have a real life to consider, both in terms of time and finances.  *wry grin*<br>
<br>
All my love to DAoC fans...just don't harass me for sticking it out with EQ.<br>
<br>
Oh, and by the way, I'm all for a fascist response, too.  Naming is a bit rough...I'll give them one opportunity to change it.  But ooc behaviour over shout/auction deserves one warning, then a character deletion.  On the positive side, though, I've noticed more and more that OOC shouts in FV get flat ignored - like &quot;Dings!&quot; and d00d speak.<br>
<br>
Kitreana<br>
Druid of Tunare<br>
Saryrn<br>
* * * * *<br>
Sahira<br>
Druid of Karana<br>
