<br>
Believe me, if it weren't for a few things, I wouldn't have been able to do both either.  I'm very fortunate to have such an opportunity.<br>
<br>
I was in Dark Age beta just as the 4th Beta came out, so I've got a couple of months experience working with the development team and there is simply a world of difference in the approach.  I am not saying this to rub it in... I am saying it with hope that Verant will get it's act together.  <br>
<br>
In the same turn, I have worked closely with most facets of EverQuest behind the scenes, and I can say from my experiences that the developers, guides and GMs all are doing the absolute best they can.  It is up to the corporation of Verant to wake up and change their policies and approach.  The paid staff as well as the volunteers get a lot of grief over simply doing their jobs.  The number one bottleneck with EverQuest is the top brass.  The situation now is that Dark Age is just the first of the games coming out that are specifically targeting the two years of complaints against the design of EQ and will be syphoning out players... and believe me when it isn't the punks and griefers that are flooding to Dark Age.  Why would they, when they are being forced to follow the rules and are limited in how they can screw people over?  They may as well stay in EQ, where they can get away with it.<br>
<br>
I love EverQuest, and I remember when it was light years ahead of anything else out there, including UO.  But Verant has sat like a fat cat and ignored their customer's begging and pleading and are about to see the results.  I hope for everyone's sake that this is the 'first step' for Verant getting a change in attitude and fixing the problems not only in the game design, but in the approach to customer service (the rules, not the people).<br>
<br>
Can someone move this to the OC or Soapbox section?  I think I just ranted.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugorgash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gorgash</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.shadowguard.org/resources/skull15-2.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 46<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(10/16/01 12:34:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm9.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=36.topic&index=14>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: DAOC RP Server to deput at launch</span><hr size=1> Hmmm. Actually I've only seen grief from folks hassling others because they WANT to try DAOC. I have yet to see anyone that plays DAOC to hassle someone that won't try DAOC, other than to say &quot;I like DAOC.&quot;    <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START ;) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/wink.gif ALT=";)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
